edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.bitstream
Class BitstreamParser

java.lang.Object
  edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.bitstream.BitstreamParser

public class BitstreamParser
extends java.lang.Object

Parses an existing binary bitfile (.bit) and generates a Bitstream object. TODO: Look into the different file formats and be able to parse any of them and also to generate any of them. See page 53 of Xilinx configuration guide (ug071.pdf).

Static method to return a Bitstream objet from a filename. This static method has built in exit code if there are problems with the bitstream parsing.

createBody

protected PacketList createBody(int numHeaderBytes)
                         throws BitstreamException
Creates the bitstream packets from the bit file. A packet header is 4 bytes converted to an integer. The header is parsed and the number of data words is determined. Data words will be created from 4 consecutive bytes.

Throws:
BitstreamException

getWordAsInt

public static int getWordAsInt(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Byte> bytes,
                               int start)
Creates an integer from the bit file using the 4 bytes starting with the byte specified by start. See also AddDataToPacket().

Parameters:
start - This is a byte offset into the file at which the data for a packet can be created.
